

In order to install e-Studio CMS:

1. Configure your database and add its configuration parameters to the config file (please use your own database configuration):

  database:
    estudio:
      dsn: 'mysql:host=localhost;dbname=estudio'
      username: estudio
      password: estudio
      
   $ mysql -u root -p
   
   mysql> create database estudio;
   mysql> grant all privileges on estudio.* to 'estudio'@'localhost' identified by 'estudio';
   mysql> flush privileges;

2. Add e-studio to the included add-ons at your application configuration:

  tecnodesign:
    addons:
      estudio: true

3. Add at least one configuration line, to enable e-Studio self-installation:

  e-studio:
    install: true

4. Run: [apps-dir]$ ./[project-name] e-studio-install

5. Remove or unset the self-installation configuration directive.
